721019f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, at E. 50th Street, showing the distinctive Hotel Beverly as photographed across the new Waldorf Astoria site. Occupying the remaining corners are the Cathedral High School and the 3 story Fire Dept. Truck No. 2. Surrounding the latter is the 15 story Montclair. View 3 details these last two item.
May 3, 1930
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
